14/06/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Foreign Minister Ivaylo Kalfin welcomed on Tuesday (13 June) indications that Libya plans to speed up proceedings against five Bulgarian nurses and one Palestinian doctor. 
They are facing a new trial for allegedly infecting children with HIV. 
Kalfin spoke to reporters in Sofia after learning the Tripoli court handling the case has scheduled its next session for 20 June. 
The court indicated it plans to convene weekly, and agreed to accept new evidence and hear from new witnesses. 
(BNR, BTA, Darik - 13/06/06)
